          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1095_step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine <strong>half</strong> of the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> (not a fan of raw garlic? Just add a little!) with your <strong>mayo</strong>,<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and splash of<strong> cold water </strong>in a small bowl – this is your<strong> garlic mayo</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 2? Save the remaining chopped garlic for another recipe!</p><p>Combine the<strong> drained sweetcorn</strong>,<strong> chopped cherry tomatoes</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>and<strong> </strong>the juice of half your <strong>lime wedges<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> in a separate bowl – this is your<strong> corn salsa</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1095_step-5-x200.jpg",
